segment as well as the utilization of a wide range of rubber 
products. On average, manufacturers of carbon black have 
been able to profit from the sound development of the auto-
motive market in the past eight years. Global production of 
passenger cars rose from 42 million units in 2003 to almost 
60 million units in 2011, with utility vehicles adding a fur-
ther 20 million units that year. In 2010 the global stock of 
all vehicles surpassed the 1 billion mark for the first time.
Unsurprisingly, Asia Pacific is found to be the main driv-
er for growth; consumption and production volumes in this 
region are both expected to increase by more than 4.5% 
per annum. China dominates the market, single-handedly 
consuming >30% of the total global carbon black market 
volume. As a result of massive expansions in capacity, this 
region will become a net exporter in the future.
