, 1,2-benzenedicarboxylicacid, di-C8-10-
branched alkyl esters; and DIDP
, 1,2-benzenedicarboxyli-
cacid, di-C9-11-branched alkyl esters. Phthalates are used 
as plasticizers for a variety of polymers, including rubber 
and nitrocellulose.
Analytical laboratories, regulatory bodies and manu-
facturers will all use ASTM D7823 to determine wheth-
er a product meets the requirements of Section 108 of 
the CPSIA law. Childrens toys and child care articles 
that can be placed in the mouth are among the products 
covered by ASTM D7823 and the CPSIA. In addition 
to CPSIA, other regulations on these phthalates include 
the European Union Directive 2005/84/EC and Japans 
Health, Labor and Welfare Ministry Guideline No. 336 
(2010).
